Figure 23 . Sample means and standard deviations for different quantities over the whole dataset of geometries, divided according to the corresponding batch
(from 0 to 29, in the x x -axis).
First row: maximum velocity magnitude at peak systole ( t = 2.16 t=2.16 s);
second row: largest pressure difference between inlet and descending aorta over the cardiac cycle;
third row: mean wall shear stress magnitude over the whole blood vessel wall and over the cardiac cycle;
Fourth row: mean oscillatory shear index over a reference patch on the underside of the descending aorta.
Black: α r = 1.3 \alpha_{r}=1.3 (30% radius increase), blue: α r = 1 \alpha_{r}=1 , red: α r = 0.7 \alpha_{r}=0.7 (30% radius decrease).
